[3] Viet Nam (Ho Chi Minh City)
Date: Thu 11 Dec 2008
Source: Thanh Nien News [edited]
<http://www.thanhniennews.com/healthy/?catid=8&newsid=44485>


Dengue cases up by 35 percent in HCMC [Ho Chi Minh City]
--------------------------------------------------------
Ho Chi Minh City has so far this year [2008] recorded nearly 14 000
cases of dengue fever or a 35 percent year-on-year increase, a senior
city health official has said.

Dr Nguyen Dac Tho, deputy director of the city's Preventive Health
Center was addressing a meeting on preventing and fighting epidemics
held Wednesday [10 Dec 2008].

He said while the city has managed to control somewhat the spread of
the mosquito-borne fever, the situation remained complicated.

Districts 6, 8, 10, 11, Tan Binh, and Tan Phu are still the worst hit areas.

Tho also cautioned district health agencies against ignoring malaria
as a threat, noting a patient had recently died because it was
discovered too late.

[Byline: Thanh Tung]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-MBDS
<promed-mbds@promedmail.org>

[The number of dengue fever cases reported from Ho Chi Minh City is
still increasing with total cases of 14 000 reported during 2008 --
representing an increase from 10 000 cases and 5 deaths reported on
25 Oct 2008 (see prior PRO/MBDS posting Dengue - Viet Nam (16): Ho
Chi Minh City 20081025.3368). As of 25 Nov 2008, a total of 78 512
cases and 79 deaths of dengue fever had been recorded nationwide,
while the 20 southern cities and provinces have reported 58 635 cases
and 69 deaths in 2008 (see prior PRO/MBDS posting Dengue - Viet Nam
(20) 20081126.3720).

For maps of Viet Nam with provinces, see
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/vietnam_admin01.jpg> and
<http://www.angelfire.com/co/hongnam/vnmap.html>.
The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Viet Nam can be accessed at
<http://healthmap.org/promed?v=14.9,108.5,5>.
This map shows other outbreaks in Viet Nam and surrounding countries
that have been reported on ProMED-mail. The postings can be directly
accessed through this map. - Mods.YMA/MPP]

