[5] St Martin
Date: Wed 10 Dec 2008
Source: Institut de Veille Sanitaire, Point Epidemiologique no. 33
[in French, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.invs.sante.fr/presse/2008/le_point_sur/dengue_pep_st_barth_101208/pep_sbsm_2008_32_dengue.pdf>


Magnitude of the epidemic
-------------------------
During [epidemiological] week 49 [1-7 Dec 2008] of 2008, we estimated
that 145 people have consulted a general practitioner for a clinical
syndrome suggestive of dengue [virus infection]. The number of
laboratory confirmed [dengue] cases is also above the maximum levels
expected for many weeks, without a decreasing trend. The rate of
positive serological tests remains stable at around 40 percent.

Severity of the epidemic
------------------------
Since early December [2008], 2 laboratory confirmed cases were
hospitalized, 1 adult for DHF, and 1 child for a classical dengue
fever. Since the epidemic began, 16 people have been hospitalized: 10
adults including 3 severe forms and a dengue hemorrhagic fever [DHF]
[case], and 4 children (with classical dengue fever). No deaths from
dengue have been recorded since the beginning of the epidemic.

[Dengue virus] serotypes circulating
------------------------------------
DEN-1 virus (60 percent [of cases]) with DEN-2 virus co-circulating
since the epidemic began. DEN-4 virus was identified for the 1st time
during the month of October [2008]. On the Dutch part of the island,
these 3 viruses are circulating also.

--
